Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} into the pan, skin-side down. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until the skin is golden, ~{5-6%minutes}, then turn and cook for ~{1%minute} on the other side.

Transfer the chicken to a #baking tray{}, skin-side up, and roast the chicken on the top shelf of your oven until cooked, ~{18-25%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the tagliatelle.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @chives{1%bunch}(finely chopped) (use #scissors{} if easier). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}(halved).

In a medium #bowl{}, combine the tomatoes, @balsamic glaze{12%ml} and @olive oil{1/2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

Add the @fresh tagliatelle{200%g} to your pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @olive oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and @diced chorizo{60%g}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @water{100%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, @butter{20%g} and half the chives until melted.

When the chicken is cooked, allow it to rest for a few minutes, then cut into 1cm thick slices.

Add the cooked pasta to the sauce and toss to coat. Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick. Taste, and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the dressing bowl, then toss to coat.

Share the chorizo tagliatelle alfredo between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sliced chicken and sprinkle over the remaining chives.

Serve with the rocket salad alongside.

Enjoy!